# TiffinConnect V3.0 Design System: Vendor Panel Style Guide

This document captures the styling specifications for the TiffinConnect Vendor (Tiffin Provider) Panel. Following the V3.0 redesign, the vendor panel has been normalized for maximum readability and a premium operational feel, aligning with the core design principles of the Admin Panel.

---

## 1. Typography & Normalization (The "Readable" Standard)

We have moved away from overly technical and aesthetic stylings to prioritize functional clarity.

### 1.1 Font Hierarchy
- **Body Text**: `Inter` (Sans-serif) - used for all descriptions, list items, and form values.
- **Headings**: `Plus Jakarta Sans` or `Inter` (Bold) - used for primary section titles.
- **Normalization Rules**:
  - **Removed `font-black`**: Replaced with `font-bold` (700) or `font-semibold` (600).
  - **Case Standard**: Sentence Case or Title Case is preferred over All-Caps for better legibility.
  - **Label Sizes**: Standardized labels to `text-xs` or `text-sm` with `font-semibold`.

### 1.2 Terminology Transformation
We use standard business terms instead of "aesthetic" technical jargon:
- **Registry/Node** → **Business/Profile**
- **Telemetry/Broadcasting** → **Status/Online**
- **Sentiment Index** → **Customer Reviews**
- **Capital Velocity** → **Earnings Reports**

---

## 2. Core Components

### 2.1 The Signature Block (`.premium-card`)
Every major section is wrapped in a high-visibility card:
- **Border**: `1px solid hsla(var(--primary), 0.5)` (The "Emerald" Green Border).
- **Radius**: `2.5rem` (Extremely rounded for a modern look).
- **Background**: `bg-card/30 backdrop-blur-xl`.
- **Spacing**: `p-10 lg:p-14` for main containers; `p-8` for dashboard cards.

### 2.2 Navigation (Sidebar & Header)
- **Vendor Identity**: Uses the "👨‍🍳" icon in the sidebar branding.
- **Group Label**: "Vendor Dashboard" (text-xs, font-bold, tracking-widest).
- **Nav Items**: Height `h-11`, Rounded `rounded-xl`, Hover `bg-muted/30`.
- **Active State**: Emerald glow (`bg-primary/10`, `text-primary`, `border-primary/20`).

---

## 3. Page-Specific Styles

### 3.1 Order Management ([IncomingOrdersPage.tsx](file:///e:/DELTA/M%20A%20I%20N%20M%20A%20I%20N/FULL%20STACK%20DEPLOYES%20PROJECTS/TiffinConnect/tiffin-connect-hub-59/src/pages/vendor/IncomingOrdersPage.tsx))
- **Task Console**: Centered layout using `max-w-4xl` for focus.
- **Order Cards**: 
  - Status badges use the V3 standard (Green for Completed, Amber for Pending).
  - Meal names use `text-xl font-bold tracking-tight`.
- **Action Buttons**: `h-14`, `rounded-xl`, high contrast for primary actions.

### 3.2 Menu & Resources ([MenuManagementPage.tsx](file:///e:/DELTA/M%20A%20I%20N%20M%20A%20I%20N/FULL%20STACK%20DEPLOYES%20PROJECTS/TiffinConnect/tiffin-connect-hub-59/src/pages/vendor/MenuManagementPage.tsx))
- **Menu Grid**: Responsive grid (`grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-8`).
- **Item Badges**: `badge-premium` for price and availability status.
- **Empty State**: Simple center-aligned layout with `w-24 h-24` icons and friendly "Setup Menu" calls to action.

### 3.3 Financial Hub ([EarningsPage.tsx](file:///e:/DELTA/M%20A%20I%20N%20M%20A%20I%20N/FULL%20STACK%20DEPLOYES%20PROJECTS/TiffinConnect/tiffin-connect-hub-59/src/pages/vendor/EarningsPage.tsx))
- **Stats Row**: 4-column grid showing Today, Week, Month, and Total revenue.
- **Visualization**: `NumberTicker` component for dynamic "count-up" effects on currency values.
- **Breakdown List**: Items use `rounded-2xl`, `bg-muted/20`, and `border-primary/20`.

### 3.4 Feedback Stream ([VendorReviewsPage.tsx](file:///e:/DELTA/M%20A%20I%20N%20M%20A%20I%20N/FULL%20STACK%20DEPLOYES%20PROJECTS/TiffinConnect/tiffin-connect-hub-59/src/pages/vendor/VendorReviewsPage.tsx))
- **Review Cards**: Flex layout (`flex-col lg:flex-row`).
- **Rating Stars**: Primary color (`fill-primary`) for filled stars, muted for empty.
- **Quote Block**: Italicized `text-lg` with a subtle `Quote` icon background.

---

## 4. Interaction & Motion

### 4.1 Framer Motion Patterns
- **Entry Fades**: All pages and cards animate in with `initial={{ opacity: 0, y: 20 }} animate={{ opacity: 1, y: 0 }}`.
- **AnimatePresence**: Used for tab switching and empty-state transitions to prevent "jumping" content.
- **Hover Effects**: Subtly maintained but minimized to ensure high performance and "Always Visible" borders.

### 4.2 Utility Classes
- **`.scrollbar-hide`**: Applied to the main content area for a clean, app-like feel.
- **`.badge-premium`**: Standard emerald badge used for titles and highlights.

---

## 5. Styling Philosophy (V3.0)
> **"Readable, Reliable, Remarkable."**
> 
> The Vendor dashboard should feel like a High-Performance tool, not a tech demo. Every border is visible, every button is clickable, and every metric is legible at a glance. Avoid thin weights or low-contrast text. Use the Emerald accent (`--primary`) to guide the vendor's focus to what matters most: Orders and Earnings.
